				<p>With full step, both phases are always on resulting in more torque for the same current setting. I posted the above comment (about jitter) because jitter in the step period can have a similar effect as reduced torque and can have a greater effect with microstepping if a higher frequency step pulse is used in order to achieve the same rotation rate.</p>
